thread.title_full: Prep soccer: L-B blanks C-R on senior night

author: The Courier
title: Prep soccer: L-B blanks C-R on senior night
text:
Comment: 0 
Five Liberty-Benton players each scored a goal to power the Eagles to a 5-0 North Central Ohio Soccer Association boys win over Cory-Rawson. Brendan Wolford, Chad Frommer, Austin Patrick, Connor Oldaker and Logan Young scored one goal apiece to help the Eagles improve to 8-6-1 overall and 4-1-1 in the NCOSA. Logan Young and Allen and Brandon Bracy were both credited with assists. The Eagles had a 15-1 edge in shots as goalkeeper Storm Shepherd posted his third shutout of the season. Keith Edwards had 10 saves for the Hornets (2-12, 1-6 NCOSA). Ty Waltz recorded nine intercepts and three steals to lead Liberty-Benton defensively.
